OL,7,FHe also described the months of
OL,8,Funravelling what had happened as the
OL,9,Fworst year in his life
OL,11,FClarke was described by others in the
OL,12,Fcongregation as "the heart and soul of
OL,13,Fthe church" and a trusted figure.
OL,15,FThe court was also told Clarke was
OL,16,Fsomeone who had a "big heart" and was
OL,17,Fnot a bad person but had made "poor
OL,18,Fchoices".
